    "updated_at": "2016-04-28T15:24:32Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "These are two separate questions:\n1. protobuf is used because it has schema, and it is much more efficient and faster than JSON. (proto3 still has JSON bindings). https://developers.google.com/protocol-buffers/docs/overview#what-are-protocol-buffers\n2. HTTP2 is used for many good reasons: HTTP2 is a standard and HTTP protocol is well known to proxies, firewalls and many software tools. The streaming nature of HTTP2 suits our needs very well, so no need to reinvent the wheel. We'll probably post more on this topic soon on grpc.io page.\n\nNext time, please consider posting general questions like this on stackoverflow or grpc.io mailing list.\n"
  },
